  "text": "The crd_client.go implementation follows the Kubernetes client-go patterns for creating typed custom resource clients. The design patterns were studied from the core/v1 package typed clients (kubernetes/typed/core/v1/configmap.go, pod.go, namespace.go) and the core_client.go which shows how to structure a group client. The implementation uses rest.Interface from rest/client.go for the underlying HTTP client abstraction, following the same patterns used in client-go. The request building chain uses rest/request.go methods (Post, Get, Delete) along with VersionedParams for parameter encoding, Namespace for namespace scoping, Resource for resource specification, and Name for resource identification. The scheme/register.go provides the ParameterCodec, Scheme, and Codecs required for proper serialization/deserialization. The gentype/type.go package demonstrates the generic type patterns used by generated Kubernetes clients, which influenced the design of this custom resource client. The Widget custom resource from the example.com/v1 API group is implemented with proper context.Context propagation in all CRUD operations (Create, Get, List, Delete), matching the signatures and conventions established in the kubernetes/typed/ clients. The client initialization follows the pattern from core_client.go with NewForConfig and New factory functions that properly configure the rest.Config with the custom API group version and paths."
}

